  "prompt": "What are the disadvantages of using Angular?",
  "response": "Here are some key disadvantages of using Angular:\n\n1. Performance Limitations\n- Complex two-way data binding can slow down application performance\n- Steeper learning curve compared to other frameworks\n- Larger bundle size compared to lightweight frameworks\n\n2. Complexity\n- Steep learning curve for beginners\n- Complex component architecture\n- Requires understanding of TypeScript\n- Multiple ways to solve the same problem can lead to confusion\n\n3. Version Migration Challenges\n- Significant differences between Angular versions\n- Frequent major version updates can require substantial code refactoring\n- Migration between versions can be time-consuming\n\n4. Overengineered Architecture\n- Verbose and complex configuration\n- Heavyweight framework with many built-in features\n- Can be overkill for small to medium-sized projects\n\n5. Memory Leaks\n- Potential memory leaks if not managed properly\n- Requires careful handling of component lifecycle\n- Need for explicit memory management and subscription handling\n\n6. Dependency Injection Complexity\n- Complex dependency injection system\n- Can be challenging to understand and implement correctly\n- Additional overhead in terms of performance\n\n7. Limited SEO Capabilities\n- Single-page applications (SPAs) can have SEO challenges\n- Requires additional configuration for server-side rendering\n- Initial page load might be slower\n\n8. Development Speed\n- More setup and boilerplate code compared to other frameworks\n- Longer compilation times\n- More complex development process\n\n9. Browser Compatibility\n- Some older browsers might not fully support Angular features\n- Requires additional polyfills for complete compatibility\n\n10. Opinionated Framework\n- Strict and opinionated structure\n- Less flexibility compared to other frameworks\n- Developers must follow Angular's specific patterns and conventions\n\nThese disadvantages don't necessarily mean Angular is a bad choice. The framework still offers robust features and is suitable for large-scale enterprise applications. The key is to evaluate your project's specific requirements and choose accordingly.",
